title: colour Macro
type: text/vnd.tiddlywiki
caption: colour

The <<.def colour>> (or <<.def color>>) macro returns the [[CSS|Cascading Style Sheets]] value of one of the colours in the current [[palette|ColourPalettes]].

The colour is read from the [[compiled palette|ColourPalettes]] in <<.tid "$:/temp/palette-colours">>. If the current palette does not define the colour, the value is taken from the configuration tiddler `$:/config/DefaultColourMappings/<colour-name>`, which must contain a plain CSS colour value. This enables plugins to ship defaults for colours that are not present in the core palettes.

<<.from-version "5.5.0">> The macro is implemented as a [[function|Functions]], so it can also be used as the value of a widget attribute, or called within a filter:

```
<div style.background-color=<<colour page-background>>>
```

```
[function[colour],[page-background]]
```

!! Parameters

;name
: The name of the palette entry, e.g. `page-background`

